<div style="padding-left:10px;">
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: justify; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><strong><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"><br></span></strong></p><p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: justify; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><strong><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">PAYMENT SYSTEMS IN GHANA</span></strong></p>
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: left; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: left; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"><strong>OVERVIEW</strong></span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: justify; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">The payment system is the entire matrix of institutional infrastructure arrangements and processes in a country set up to enable economic agents (individuals, businesses, organisations and Government) initiate and transfer monetary claims in the form of commercial and central bank liabilities.</span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: left; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: justify; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Ghana''s payment system has improved significantly since 1997 when the MICR cheques were introduced, and continues to evolve to meet the developmental needs&nbsp;of the country. The current trend in Ghana''s payment systems development is being&nbsp;driven by economic, financial, public policy factors as well as a growing local ICT industry and global trends in payment systems development.</span></p>
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: left; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px; WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: left; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; MARGIN-TOP: 0px; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">The development of payment and settlement systems in&nbsp;Ghana has been premised on the following key objectives:</span></p>
<ul style="WHITE-SPACE: normal; WORD-SPACING: 0px; TEXT-TRANSFORM: none; COLOR: rgb(51,51,51); TEXT-ALIGN: left; FONT: 12px Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; WIDOWS: 1; LETTER-SPACING: normal; BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,255); TEXT-INDENT: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px">
<li style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">To prevent and or contain risks in payment, clearing and settlement systems;<br></span></li>
<li style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">To establish a robust oversight and regulatory regime for the payment and settlement systems;<br></span></li>
<li style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">To bring efficiency to fiscal operations of the Ghana Government<br></span></li>
<li style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">To deepen financial intermediation;<br></span></li>
<li style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">To discourage the use of cash for transactions whilst encouraging the use of paper-based instruments for payments as part of the short-term development plan;<br></span></li>
<li style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">To promote financial inclusion without risking the safety and soundness of the banking system; and<br></span></li>
<li style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 5px"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">To develop an integrated electronic payment infrastructure that will enhance interoperability of payment and securities infrastructures.</span></li></ul></div>
';
